y of [[The Beatles]] song [[Ticket to Ride (song)]].\n |LineColor=6699FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=45\n |EpisodeNumber2=19\n |Title=Deadwood Kid\n |DirectedBy=Alan Simmonds\n |WrittenBy=Michael Mercer\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|1|5}}\n |ProdCode=219\n |ShortSummary=Alec, Nicole, and The Black find themselves in a ghost town at the mercy of a deluded man who has a plan for The Black's future.\n |LineColor=6699FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=46\n |EpisodeNumber2=20\n |Title=Horse of the Year\n |DirectedBy=Alan Simmonds\n |WrittenBy=Jana Veverka\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|1|12}}\n |ProdCode=220\n |ShortSummary=When The Black is named Horse of the Year, the success goes to Alec's head and he becomes a spoiled brat.\n |LineColor=6699FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=47\n |EpisodeNumber2=21\n |Title=If The Shoe Fits\n |DirectedBy=Peter Rowe\n |WrittenBy=Dawn Ritchie\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|1|19}}\n |ProdCode=221\n |ShortSummary=An unscrupulous vet tries to cripple The Black with the help of Nicole's father.\n |LineColor=6699FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=48\n |EpisodeNumber2=22\n |Title=Code of Silence\n |DirectedBy=Peter Rowe\n |WrittenBy=Jana Veverka\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|1|26}}\n |ProdCode=222\n |ShortSummary=A teenage motorcycle gang kidnaps The Black and leaves him to die.\n |LineColor=6699FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=49\n |EpisodeNumber2=23\n |Title=Black Tide\n |DirectedBy=Alan Simmonds\n |WrittenBy=Louise Vincent\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|2|2}}\n |ProdCode=223\n |ShortSummary=The Black is challenged by another black stallion who turns out to be The Black's son named Black Tide.\n |LineColor=6699FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=50\n |EpisodeNumber2=24\n |Title=Going, Going, Gone\n |DirectedBy=Alan Simmonds\n |WrittenBy=Dawn Ritchie\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1992|2|9}}\n |ProdCode=224\n |ShortSummary=Alec is tricked into putting The Black on the aucti