 when he goes, it is revealed Jen is in on the plan with Danny. To get their own back on Danny and Jen, the kids hatch a plan to pretend Faith left a piece of expensive jewellery behind. Faith and Rick tell this to Danny and Jen and when they mention Frank is looking after a ring, which Faith pretends is her mother's engagement ring. Later at the flat with [[#Kazima Tako|Kazima]] (Akuc Bol), Frank plans to give Danny the watch, but when Frank has the ring, Danny demands to have the ring and will exchange for all the money he has taken off Frank.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Jen}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Georgina Campbell]]}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Shopkeeper}}\n| {{nowrap|Alan Renwick}}\n| {{Anchor|Shopkeeper}} When looking for [[Frank Matthews (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Frank]] (Chris Slater), [[Rick Barber|Rick]] (Daniel Pearson), [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar), [[Tee Taylor|Tee]] ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) and [[Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) find Frank's pocket watch for sale in a window. They ask the shopkeeper if they can save the watch for them, but he tells them that he has had interest from another customer. [[#Kazima Tako|Kazima]] (Akuc Bol) later comes to buy the watch from the shopkeeper.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Community Support Officer}}\n| {{nowrap|7 February 2014}}\n| {{nowrap|Shareesa Valentine}}\n| {{Anchor|Community Support Officer}} On a day out with [[Tyler Lewis (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Tyler]] (Miles Butler-Houghton), Tyler's mother, [[#Sally Lewis|Sally]] (Diveen Henry), gets some ice cream, however, she has no money to pay, so she runs away without paying. The community support officer intercepts Sally. [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu) eventually finds Sally and Tyler and she pays for the ice cream.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Mr Jenkins}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | {{nowrap|28 February 2014}}\n| {{nowrap|Darren Morfitt}}\n| {{Anchor|Mr Jenkins}} Mr Jenkins is a football coach. After a match, he pulls [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) aside, he has a go at Bailey for letting the opposing team score more goals and when Bailey asks what his problem is, Mr Jenkins is racist towards Bailey. Bailey keeps quiet about what Mr Jenkins told him, but [[#Faith Davis|Faith]] (Leanne Dunstan) gets the truth out of Bailey and they report the incident to [[Mike Milligan (The Story of Tracy Beaker character)|Mike]] (Connor Byrne). Mike goes down to the pitch and confronts Mr Jenkins about what he said.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Justin}}\n| {{nowrap|Mackenzie Sol Williams}}\n| {{Anchor|Justin}} Justin is a teammate of [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar). When Justin makes a racist remark, Bailey physically attacks Justin.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|[[Viv Anderson]]}}\n| {{nowrap|Himself}}\n| {{Anchor|[[Viv Anderson]]}} Viv Anderson oversees football training with [[#Mr Jenkins|Mr Jenkins]] (Darren Morfitt). [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) starts playing with a football during Mr Jenkins' talk and Viv tells [[#Mike Milligan (The Story of Tracy Beaker character)|Mike]] (Connor Byrne) that Bailey needs to learn manners. When Bailey later tells Mike that Mr Johnson was racist to him, Mike goes down to the pitch and confronts Mr Johnson, which is witnessed by Viv. Viv visits The Dumping Ground and encourages Bailey not to quit due to racism as he went through it and Viv arranges to see Bailey play football again. [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu) is starstruck when she sees Viv and he gives her his football shirt.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Nicky Richardson}}\n| {{nowrap|7 March 2014}}\n| {{nowrap|Lu Corfield}}\n| {{Anchor|Nicky Richardson}} When someone attempts to rob Nicky outside The Dumping Ground, [[Johnny Taylor (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Johnny Taylor]] (Joe Maw) takes a photo of the person who attempted to take her bag. Johnny tells Nicky that he managed to get a photo and Nicky thanks him before handing him a card with her contact details and Johnny realises she is in the army. Johnny decides to see Nicky about joining the army. When Johnny fails at a teamwork task, he goes to see Nicky, who tells him that he is not a quitter as he persevered.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Doug}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" | {{nowrap|14 March 2014}}\n| {{nowrap|Michael Hodgson}}\n| {{Anchor|Doug}} rowspan=\"2\" | Doug and Nerys are potential adoptive parents for [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson). Floss believes she will continue living at The Dumping Ground, but [[Harry Jones (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Harry]] (Philip Graham Scott) tells Floss what adoption really means. When Floss goes to the park with Nerys, Doug and [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu), a boy named [[#Jesse|Jesse]] (Alex Humprey) upsets Floss when he presumes Floss doesn't have a mum, so Floss pushes him in retaliation. Floss brings [[Tee Taylor|Tee]] ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) on a visit to Doug and Nerys' house. After making play dough, Nerys goes to clean Floss' hand, she decides to remove the nail varnish, but Floss knocks the flour on the floor and she then throws all the other play dough ingredients out of the dishes. Floss decides that she doesn't want to be adopted by Doug and Nerys.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Nerys}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Lucy Speed]]}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Neil}}\n| {{nowrap|John Bowley}}\n| {{Anchor|Neil}} Neil is the ex-boyfriend of [[Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]). Carmen breaks up with Neil after their date.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Jesse's Mum}}\n| {{nowrap|Claire Sundin}}\n| {{Anchor|Jesse's Mum}} rowspan=\"2\" | When [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson) goes to the park with [[#Nerys|Nerys]] ([[Lucy Speed]]), [[#Doug|Doug]] (Michael Hodgson) and [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu), [[#Jesse|Jesse]] (Alex Humprey) upsets Floss when he presumes Floss doesn't have a mum, so Floss pushes Jesse in retaliation.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Jesse}}\n| {{nowrap|Alex Humprey}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Hope Taylor}}\n| {{nowrap|21 March 2014, 13 March 2015}}\n| {{nowrap|Lucy Briggs (2014) <br> Holly and Paige Robinson (2015)}}\n| {{Anchor|Hope}} Hope is the daughter of [[#Keith|Keith]] ([[Neil Morrissey]]) and [[#Lucy|Lucy]] ([[Sally Rogers]]) as well as the younger half-sister of [[Johnny Taylor (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Johnny]] (Joe Maw) and [[Tee Taylor|Tee]] ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]). Feeling that Hope isn't safe with Lucy, Tee takes Hope whilst Lucy is distracted and takes her to The Dumping Ground before pretending to [[Mike Milligan (The Story of Tracy Beaker character)|Mike]] (Connor Byrne) she is an abandoned child. A frantic Lucy turns up at The Dumping Ground to collect Hope and Mike realises that Hope is Johnny and Tee's sister.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Sian da Silva}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|28 March 2014}}\n| {{nowrap|Gabrielle Glaister}}\n| {{Anchor|Sian}} Sian is a council representative. When [[Frank Matthews (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Frank]] (Chris Slater) is sacked from his job after a short period of time, he goes to apologise to Sian and asks if she can get [[#Faith Davis|Faith]] (Leanne Dunstan) her job back, but she refuses. [[Harry Jones (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Harry]] (Philip Graham Scott) and [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson) go to the town hall with Frank to invite Sian to The Dumping Ground for lunch, but she declines, even when they mention that [[Mike Milligan (The Story of Tracy Beaker character)|Mike]] (Connor Byrne) will be there. Sian comes to lunch and Mike asks Sian to go for dinner with him and Sian accepts.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Manager}}\n| {{nowrap|John Sumner}}\n| {{Anchor|Manager}} The manager of a leisure centre, where [[Frank Matthews (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Frank]] (Chris Slater) gets a job and where [[#Faith Davis|Faith]] (Leanne Dunstan) does her work placement. When Frank spots [[Liam O'Donovan|Liam]] ([[Richard Wisker]]), Frank starts physically attacking Liam and Faith tries to stop Frank. Frank and Faith are both sacked by the manager.\n|}\n\n===Series 3 (2015)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Character\n! Date(s)\n! Actor\n! Circumstances\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Police Officer}}\n| rowspan=\"7\" | {{nowrap|16 January 2015}}\n| {{nowrap|Amer Nazir}}\n| {{Anchor|Police Officer (series 3 episode 1)}} At the end of a fostering information day, guests find out that their purses and wallets have been taken. The police officer questions who had access to them and if anyone left early. [[#Stephanie Branston|Stephanie]] ([[Charlie Brooks]]) accuses [[#Sally Lewis|Sally]] (Diveen Henry). [[Johnny Taylor (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Johnny]] (Joe Maw) is questioned by the police officer when a wallet is found in the bathroom in his room, handed in by [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar).\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Stephanie Branston}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Charlie Brooks]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Stephanie Branston}} rowspan=\"2\" | Stephanie and Matt Branston attend the fostering information day. [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) and [[Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) both try and impress Stephanie and Matt so that they will foster either of them. Bailey confronts Stephanie and Matt about them being accused of racism, so Bailey suggests if they foster him, it will prove to people they are not racist. When the bath is over filled, the ceiling leaks and comes through, soaking Stephanie, Matt and Carmen and when Stephanie calls the kids rejects, Carmen realises that she doesn't want to be fostered by Stephanie and Matt. When the guests are about to leave, they find that their purses and wallets have been taken and Stephanie believes [[#Sally Lewis|Sally]] (Diveeen Henry) is responsible.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Matt Branston}}\n| {{nowrap|Stuart Manning}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Mr Gordon}}\n| {{nowrap|Grant Burgin}}\n| {{Anchor|Mr Gordon}} row