h him. Sasha agrees, but she learns that Tommo and her would have to shoplift and she stays way The Dumping Ground.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Peter}}\n| {{nowrap|Ian Kershaw}}\n| {{Anchor|Peter (series 4)}} When [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]) breaks into a house, Peter catches her.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Phoebe}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" | {{nowrap|25 March 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Tanya Vital}}\n| {{Anchor|Phoebe}} rowspan=\"3\"| Phoebe, Mary and Kerr are temporary care workers to cover for [[#Mike Milligan|Mike]] (Connor Byrne). The kids ask her questions on what makes her better than Mike. Phoebe leaves when an argument breaks out after it emerges [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) reported Mike to the police and explains to May-Li that she can't deal with the amount of anger. Mary explains her husband died the previous year and that she was a foster carer. Mary cooks dinner, but she leaves when she realises how much the kids miss and love Mike. Kerr gets the kids to participate in a treasure hunt, but he makes fun of [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]]'s (Kasey McKellar) spelling. The kids tell him Bailey is dyslexic, but he believes Bailey is lazy.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Mary}}\n| {{nowrap|Liz Crawther}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Kerr}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Matt Kennard]]}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Chair Person}}\n| {{nowrap|Judith Alexander}}\n| {{Anchor|Chair Person}} The chair person who holds [[#Mike Milligan|Mike]]'s (Connor Byrne) discipline hearing. The kids burst in the meeting with [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]]'s ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) file and after pleading with them, Mike is given his job back.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Lou}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|30 September 2016 \u2013 7 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Warwick Davis]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Lou}} rowspan=\"2\"| Lou and Ange are potential adoptive parents for [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]). On a trip to the seaside, it becomes clear Sasha is not ready to 