uttery) gets [[Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) to tell him about his business. Duncan presents the prize to a girl named Maya Young.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Hollie}}\n| {{nowrap|Leah Walker}}\n| {{Anchor|Hollie}} Hollie is a girl [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) meets at the opening of the Young Entrepreneur of the Year competition. After helping Hollie out at the park, Hollie and Bailey decide to combine their business and go to London for a marketing workshop. Bailey reveals to Hollie he lives in a children's home and takes a lighthearted comment from Hollie seriously. Hollie visits Bailey and the pair collect references and Bailey is invited to dinner at Hollie's, where she gives him the money for London. Back at The Dumping Ground, Bailey is arrested when customers accuse him of stealing money, but Hollie confesses to taking it. Bailey chooses to have nothing more to do with Hollie.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Simon}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Chris Jack]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Simon}} Simon is the father of [[#Hollie|Hollie]] (Leah Walker), who is impressed with [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) when Hollie brings him to dinner. However, Simon takes a dislike to Bailey when he is accused of stealing money and arrested, however, Hollie confesses to stealing it.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Princess}}\n| {{nowrap|Guinness}}\n| {{Anchor|Princess}} Princess is [[#Hollie|Hollie]]'s (Leah Walker) pet dog. Princess and [[#Mischief|Mischief]] (Sage) take a liking to each other.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Iona}}\n| {{nowrap|21 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Calita Rainford}}\n| {{Anchor|Iona}} Iona is an artist [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson) meets when she tries to raise money so the young people can go on their adventure trip. Floss and [[#Finn McLaine|Finn]] ([[Ruben Reuter]]) takes [[#Tee Taylor|Tee]]'s ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) to show Iona and try to persuade her to buy it. Iona refuses to and Floss tells lies about Finn in order to get h