 tells [[#Mike Milligan (The Story of Tracy Beaker character)|Mike]] (Connor Byrne) that Bailey needs to learn manners. When Bailey later tells Mike that Mr Johnson was racist to him, Mike goes down to the pitch and confronts Mr Johnson, which is witnessed by Viv. Viv visits The Dumping Ground and encourages Bailey not to quit due to racism as he went through it and Viv arranges to see Bailey play football again. [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu) is starstruck when she sees Viv and he gives her his football shirt.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Nicky Richardson}}\n| {{nowrap|7 March 2014}}\n| {{nowrap|Lu Corfield}}\n| {{Anchor|Nicky Richardson}} When someone attempts to rob Nicky outside The Dumping Ground, [[Johnny Taylor (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Johnny Taylor]] (Joe Maw) takes a photo of the person who attempted to take her bag. Johnny tells Nicky that he managed to get a photo and Nicky thanks him before handing him a card with her contact details and Johnny realises she is in the army. Johnny decides to see Nicky about joining the army. When Johnny fails at a teamwork task, he goes to see Nicky, who tells him that he is not a quitter as he persevered.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Doug}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" | {{nowrap|14 March 2014}}\n| {{nowrap|Michael Hodgson}}\n| {{Anchor|Doug}} rowspan=\"2\" | Doug and Nerys are potential adoptive parents for [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson). Floss believes she will continue living at The Dumping Ground, but [[Harry Jones (Tracy Beaker Returns character)|Harry]] (Philip Graham Scott) tells Floss what adoption really means. When Floss goes to the park with Nerys, Doug and [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu), a boy named [[#Jesse|Jesse]] (Alex Humprey) upsets Floss when he presumes Floss doesn't have a mum, so Floss pushes him in retaliation. Floss brings [[Tee Taylor|Tee]] ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) on a visit to Doug and Nerys' house. After making play dough, Nerys goes to clean Floss' hand, she decides to remove