ises to keep an eye on things Chanelle and Tyler, but Andy isn't satisfied. [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) and [[#Jody Jackson|Jody]] ([[Kia Pegg]]) go to the magic shop to see Chanelle after a text was sent on Chanelle's phone to Tyler saying that she hates him, so Jody distracts Andy.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|Plumber/Fireman}}\n| {{nowrap|17 November 2015}}\n| {{nowrap|Sam Cassidy}}\n| {{Anchor|Plumber/Fireman}} When [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen Howle]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) accidentally flushes [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]]'s (Stacy Liu) necklace down the toilet, she thinks about what she should do. When Carmen pretends that the necklace was stolen, [[#Mo Michaels|Mo]] (Reece Buttery) goes to use the toilet, but it's blocked, so [[#Mike Milligan|Mike]] (Connor Byrne) tries to unblock it, however, his hand gets stuck. The fireman is called to get Mike out. When Carmen gets [[#Kazima Tako|Kazima]] (Akuc Bol) to help her get the necklace, the toilet ends up flooding the bathroom, so they call the plumber to mend the toilet and Carmen can only offered to pay \u00a330, which the plumber accepts.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | {{nowrap|PoPo}}\n| {{nowrap|1 December 2015}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Pik-Sen Lim]]}}\n| {{Anchor|PoPo}} PoPo is [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]]'s (Stacy Liu) grandmother. She turns up unannounced at The Dumping Ground, where May-Li isn't too pleased to see her, to ask May-Li to take over the family business. She impresses the kids with her kung-fu and May-Li agrees thar PoPo can teach the kids some. [[#Jody Jackson|Jody]] ([[Kia Pegg]]) is torn about sending her mother a birthday card, so PoPo suggests she writes her feelings into a letter, but don't send it. PoPo makes it clear to May-Li that she still doesn't accept her family as May-Li's partner is a woman and her children aren't biologically hers. May-Li decides to stay on at The Dumping Ground, but gives PoPo the chance to meet her children. Later, May-Li receives a family heirloom from PoPo, a diary 