ena, Lizzie, Floss and Sasha encounter [[#Alison|Alison]] ([[Tiana Benjamin]]), a woman claiming to be [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]]'s (Kasey McKellar) mum. Rowena confronts [[#Mike Milligan|Mike]] (Connor Byrne) about the situation and Mike assures her that situations are normally dealt with. Rowena asks to see their safeguarding procedure and incident book. The following day, Rowena and Lizzie return and speak to the kids, however, they agree to stay silent. Meanwhile, Rowena witnesses how a situation between Bailey and his dad, [[#Jimmy Wharton|Jimmy]] (Mark Theodore) is dealt with. The kids later put on the play, impressing Rowena and Lizzie.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Lizzie}}\n| {{nowrap|Kate Copeland}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Mr Twigg}}\n| {{nowrap|Abas Eijanabi}}\n| {{Anchor|Mr Twigg}} When a bear costume is ruined for their play by [[#Mischief|Mischief]] (Sage), [[#Harry Jones|Harry]] (Philip Graham Scott) and [[#Finn McLaine|Finn]] ([[Ruben Reuter]]) visit Mr Twigg at his shut down restaurant with [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu). They take the bear to borrow, but when the kids find a bag of jewels hidden, they move the bear upstairs and [[#Kazima Tako|Kazima]] (Akuc Bol) hides the jewels. Later, Mr Twigg visits and tells them that he has been repossessed and the bear is valuable and one of the items the bailiffs had listed. The kids decide to give the jewels to Mr Twigg, but find them stolen and it turns out [[#Alison|Alison]] ([[Tiana Benjamin]]) took them.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Zach}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|12 February 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Jordan Bolger}}\n| {{Anchor|Zach}} Zach is a boy, who [[#Tee Taylor|Tee]] ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) runs into at the park. Zach sends Tee a text, apologising and asking to make it up. [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]) sends a text to Zach and Tee meets Zach at a cafe, with [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) and Sasha watching them. Tee plays Squash with Zach, but arrives home after injuring her knee and Zach offers Carmen a game of squash to get her into shape. Offended by his comments, Tee, Carmen and Sasha chase him out of The Dumping Ground\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Allen}}\n| {{nowrap|Ryan Wilkinson}}\n| {{Anchor|Allen}} [[#Mo Michaels|Mo]] (Reece Buttery) is convinced there are aliens in the neighbourhood and when the other kids take the mick, Mo is determined to prove them wrong. In the park, he encounters Allen and the following time in the park, he witnesses Allen being teased by a group of boys. Mo takes Allen back to The Dumping Ground, believing he is an alien and when Allen notices Mo's alien radio equipment, he is impressed and offers to improve it to get a better signal so he can call home. Mo and [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) smuggle Allen into The Dumping Ground and they start to improve the equipment. They are interrupted by [[#Mike Milligan|Mike]] (Connor Byrne) and Allen explains things to Mike and [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li]] (Stacy Liu). The following day after completing the equipment, Allen finds it smashed and Mo admits he did it. Mo and Bailey track Allen down at home and Mo apologises for believing he was an alien. After fixing the equipment, Allen gets hold of his dad, who is working long distance and after talking with Mo, Allen's dad invites Allen and his mum to live with him.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Alex}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|26 February 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Phil Rowson}}\n| {{Anchor|Alex}} When [[#Tee Taylor|Tee]] ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) goes to college for an interview, Alex is the tutor who shows her and a group of students around. During her interview, Alex asks Tee about how she finds growing up in care. Tee messes up on a question in her interview and ends up walking out. Later, Alex tells [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) they wanted to offer Tee a place on the Arts Foundation course.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Drama Tutor}}\n| {{nowrap|Hetty Baynes Russell}}\n| {{Anchor|Drama Tutor}} When [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) accompanies [[#Tee Taylor|Tee]] to college for an interview, Carmen ends up in the Drama studio and impresses the Drama Tutor. Carmen is offered a place on the Drama course.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Tommo}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|4 March 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Melique Thompson-Dwyer}}\n| {{Anchor|Tommo}} Tommo is an old friend of [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]) and she tells him she is now in care. Tommo meets Sasha outside The Dumping Ground and tells her they can live together with his brother. He leads her to a house to break into. Sasha goes through a dog flap and goes to let Tommo in at the front, but she is caught by [[#Peter (The Dumping Ground, series 4)|Peter]] (Ian Kershaw), a man who lives there and Tommo legs it. Later, Sasha is annoyed with Tommo for leaving her, but he convinces Sasha to live with his brother with him. Sasha agrees, but she learns that Tommo and her would have to shoplift and she stays way The Dumping Ground.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Peter}}\n| {{nowrap|Ian Kershaw}}\n| {{Anchor|Peter (series 4)}} When [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]) breaks into a house, Peter catches her.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Phoebe}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" | {{nowrap|25 March 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Tanya Vital}}\n| {{Anchor|Phoebe}} rowspan=\"3\"| Phoebe, Mary and Kerr are temporary care workers to cover for [[#Mike Milligan|Mike]] (Connor Byrne). The kids ask her questions on what makes her better than Mike. Phoebe leaves when an argument breaks out after it emerges [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]] ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) reported Mike to the police and explains to May-Li that she can't deal with the amount of anger. Mary explains her husband died the previous year and that she was a foster carer. Mary cooks dinner, but she leaves when she realises how much the kids miss and love Mike. Kerr gets the kids to participate in a treasure hunt, but he makes fun of [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]]'s (Kasey McKellar) spelling. The kids tell him Bailey is dyslexic, but he believes Bailey is lazy.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Mary}}\n| {{nowrap|Liz Crawther}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Kerr}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Matt Kennard]]}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Chair Person}}\n| {{nowrap|Judith Alexander}}\n| {{Anchor|Chair Person}} The chair person who holds [[#Mike Milligan|Mike]]'s (Connor Byrne) discipline hearing. The kids burst in the meeting with [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]]'s ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) file and after pleading with them, Mike is given his job back.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Lou}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|30 September 2016 \u2013 7 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Warwick Davis]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Lou}} rowspan=\"2\"| Lou and Ange are potential adoptive parents for [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]). On a trip to the seaside, it becomes clear Sasha is not ready to give up on her family and Sasha plants goods from a souvenir shop in Ange's bag. Sasha thinks [[#Harry Jones|Harry]] (Philip Graham Scott) would be ideal for Lou and Ange and Harry agrees to get to know them.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Ange}}\n| {{nowrap|Francesca Papagno}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Doris}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | {{nowrap|7 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Sheila Hancock]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Doris}} rowspan=\"3\" | Doris is an old woman, who turns up in [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]]'s ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) salon unexpectedly. When she leaves, Carmen goes after her and Doris takes Carmen to her house. Carmen is stunned with Doris' house and dress collection and Doris allows Carmen to try a dress on. Doris is surprised Carmen is in care and Carmen is disgusted to learn Doris' son [[#Felix|Felix]] (Don Gallagher) is moving her out of her home. When Felix visits Doris the next day, Carmen defends Doris and learns Doris is being moved to an old people's home. Doris visits Carmen with Felix and explains she has dementia. Doris is given Nigel the cat, who [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson) is allergic to.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Felix}}\n| {{nowrap|Don Gallagher}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Nigel}}\n| {{nowrap|Uncredited}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Sammy Doyle}}\n| {{nowrap|14 October 2016 \u2013 28 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Roderick Gilkison}}\n| {{Anchor|Sammy Doyle}} Sammy is a boy who has to stay at The Dumping Ground for a while when his aunt is ill. He meets Carmen (Amy-Leigh Hickman) and Kazima (Akuc Bol), who tell him the rules. Sammy hears Jody's (Kia Pegg) baby stimulation doll, but ignores it as he follows the rules, but later informs Jody where it is.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|[[Duncan Bannatyne]]}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" | {{nowrap|14 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Himself}}\n| {{Anchor|[[Duncan Bannatyne]]}} Duncan gives a speech to possible contenders for the Young Entrepreneur of the Year competition and [[#Mo Michaels|Mo]] (Reece Buttery) gets [[Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) to tell him about his business. Duncan presents the prize to a girl named Maya Young.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Hollie}}\n| {{nowrap|Leah Walker}}\n| {{Anchor|Hollie}} Hollie is a girl [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) meets at the opening of the Young Entrepreneur of the Year competition. After helping Hollie out at the park, Hollie and Bailey decide to combine their business and go to London for a marketing workshop. Bailey reveals to Hollie he lives in a children's home and takes a lighthearted comment from Hollie seriously. Hollie visits Bailey and the pair collect references and Bailey is invited to dinner at Hollie's, where she gives him the money for London. Back at The Dumping Ground, Bailey is arrested when customers accuse him of stealing money, but Hollie confesses to taking it. Bailey chooses to have nothing more to do with Hollie.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Simon}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Chris Jack]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Simon}} Simon is the father of [[#Hollie|Hollie]] (Leah Walker), who is impressed with [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]] (Kasey McKellar) when Hollie brings him to dinner. However, Simon takes a dislike to Bailey when he is accused of stealing money and arrested, however, Hollie confesses to stealing it.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Princess}}\n| {{nowrap|Guinness}}\n| {{Anchor|Princess}} Princess is [[#Hollie|Hollie]]'s (Leah Walker) pet dog. Princess and [[#Mischief|Mischief]] (Sage) take a liking to each other.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Iona}}\n| {{nowrap|21 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Calita Rainford}}\n| {{Anchor|Iona}} Iona is an artist [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson) meets when she tries to raise money so the young people can go on their adventure trip. Floss and [[#Finn McLaine|Finn]] ([[Ruben Reuter]]) takes [[#Tee Taylor|Tee]]'s ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) to show Iona and try to persuade her to buy it. Iona refuses to and Floss tells lies about Finn in order to get her to change her mind. Iona contacts children's services about Floss, who contact Mike.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Aunt Peg}}\n| {{nowrap|28 October 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Jane Holman}}\n| {{Anchor|Aunt Peg}} Peg is the aunt of [[#Sammy Doyle|Sammy]] (Roderick Gilkison), who collects Sammy from The Dumping Ground.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Kara}}\n| {{nowrap|4 November 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Isobel Steele]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Kara}} [[#Mo Michaels|Mo]] (Reece Buttery) meets Kara, who is selling cakes, and falls for her. [[#Floss Guppy|Floss]] (Sarah Rayson) agrees to introduce Kara to Mo, but Mo upsets Kara when he spoils her cakes. Mo and Kara work together to bake a cake for [[#Bailey Wharton|Bailey]]'s (Kasey McKellar) birthday, which ends up burnt when Mo turns the temperature up. Mo admits to Kara what he is truly like and the pair kiss.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Jim}}\n| {{nowrap|26 November 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Samuel Holland}}\n| {{Anchor|Jim}} Jim is from children's services overseeing [[#Tee Taylor|Tee]] ([[Mia McKenna-Bruce]]) and [[#Carmen Howle|Carmen]]'s ([[Amy-Leigh Hickman]]) move and he breaks the news to Tee that a housing policy reform means they won't be housed together. The young people occupy the office and won't move unless Jim does something, but are persuaded by Tee and Carmen to give up. Tee and Carmen are overjoyed when Jim has managed to house them together.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Rosie}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|2 December 2016}}\n| {{nowrap|Zoe Iqbal}}\n| {{Anchor|Rosie}} [[#Kingsley Jackson|Kingsley]] (David Avery) introduces Rosie as his girlfriend to his sister, [[#Jody Jackson|Jody]] ([[Kia Pegg]]) and Jody lets them sell Mike's carriage clock when Kingsley owes money to a gang. Jody is trapped in a fire at Kingsley's flat and Kingsley runs off when he finds out. Zoe tells Jody that Kingsley left her in the fire.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Gary}}\n| {{nowrap|Lee Warburton}}\n| {{Anchor|Gary}} Gary is [[#Ryan Reeves|Ryan Reeves]]' (Lewis Hamilton) independent visitor who [[#Mike Milligan|Mike Milligan]] (Connor Byrne) brings into The Dumping Ground to help Ryan and his sister's. [[#Chloe Reeves|Chloe Reeves]] (Hannah Moncur), relationship. Ryan tells Gary he believes everyone loves Chloe and not him because she is nice and that he is bad. Ryan goes through with Gary's suggestion of writing a message on a balloon and then releasing it.\n|}\n\n===Series 5 (2017)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Character\n! Date(s)\n! Actor\n! Circumstances\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Edward Umbleby}}\n| {{nowrap|20 January 2017 \u2013 3 February 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Jaimie Boubezari}}\n| {{Anchor|Edward Umbleby}} Edward is the son of [[#Peter and Janet Umbleby|Peter]] ([[Simon Ludders]]) and [[#Peter and Janet Umbleby|Janet Umbleby]] ([[Alison Pargeter]]). The young people are mistaken for [[Mike Milligan (The Story of Tracy Beaker character)|Mike Milligan]] and [[#May-Li Wang|May-Li Wang]]'s children, but they tell the Umbleby's they are a children's home. [[#Floss Guppy|Floss Guppy]] (Sarah Rayson) tells Peter and Janet about the young people's lives and Mike stops their son, Edward, choking on a cherry stone and the Umbleby's tell them to leave. Edward helps [[#Kazima Tako|Kazima Tako]] (Akuc Bol), [[#Toni Trent|Toni Trent]] (Nelly Currant) and [[#Billie Trent|Billie Trent]] (Gwen Currant) leave his house when they return a doll and when [[#Archie Able|Archie Able]] (Jethro Beliba) and [[#Joseph Stubbs|Joseph Stubbs]] (Yousef Naseer) are caught in their garden accused of being intruders, Edward blames Kazima, Toni and Billie. Edward crashes his drone into Kazima's cake and Edward has to help Kazima bake another one. She decides to help Edward stand up to his father and Mr Umbleby is annoyed with Edward spending time with Kazima and playing his guitar. Kazima offers Edward's parents to stay away from him and Edward gets his guitar back.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Kev}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|20 January 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Mark Homer]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Kev}} Kev is the boyfriend of [[#Kelly Bellman|Kelly Bellman]] (Sandy Foster), the father of [[#Roddy|Roddy]] ([[Alfie Browne-Sykes]]) and his daughter with Kelly and the stepfather of [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha Bellman]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]), [[#Dexter Bellman|Dexter Bellman]] ([[Alexander Aze]]) and [[#Murphy Bellman|Murphy Bellman]]. After a football match, Kev speaks with [[#Baily Wharton|Bailey Wharton]] (Kasey McKellar) about taking up coaching and going to college in America. When Kev finds out Roddy is behind burglaries, he offers Bailey a reference for a college in America in Roddy's place.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Roddy}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Alfie Browne-Sykes]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Roddy}} Roddy is the son of [[#Kev|Kev]] ([[Mark Homer]]), the stepson of [[#Kelly Bellman|Kelly Bellman]] (Sandy Foster), the half -brother of Kev and Kelly's daughter and the stepbrother of [[#Sasha Bellman|Sasha Bellman]] ([[Annabelle Davis]]), [[#Dexter Bellman|Dexter Bellman]] ([[Alexander Aze]]) and [[#Murphy Bellman|Murphy Bellman]]. Roddy and [[#Baily Wharton|Bailey Wharton]] (Kasey McKellar) organise a football match and Roddy gets Dexter to lie that a 17-year-old player is his age. Dexter confides in Bailey about Roddy threatens him if he doesn't do what he says. Roddy catches Dexter flattening the van's tyres and Roddy warns Bailey to back off. Bailey tells Sasha about the trouble Dexter has got into and they find Dexter and Roddy. Sasha finds out Sandy is involved in Roddy's plans and she takes Dexter with Bailey. Sasha calls the police and Kev offers Bailey a reference for a college in America in place of Roddy.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Professor<br>Edwin<br>von<br>Trockelbomf III}}\n| {{nowrap|27 January 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Nigel Planer]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Edwin III}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Sophie}}\n| {{nowrap|10 February 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Caitlan Barrett Ward}}\n| {{Anchor|Sophie}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Katherine}}\n| rowspan=\"3\"|{{nowrap|17 February 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Julia Haworth]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Sophie}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Adam}}\n| {{nowrap|Andrew Hanratty}}\n| {{Anchor|Adam}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Steve}}\n| {{nowrap|Lawrence Neale}}\n| {{Anchor|Steve}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Sam}}\n| rowspan=2\"|{{nowrap|3\u201317 March 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Oliver Wellington}}\n| {{Anchor|Sam}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|George}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Paul Barber (actor)|Paul Barber]]}}\n| {{Anchor|George}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Ms Bloomfield}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|{{nowrap|10 March 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Lucy Benjamin]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Ms Bloomfield}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Raplh}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Mike Grady (actor)|Mike Grady]]\n| {{Anchor|Ralph}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Anjli}}\n| {{nowrap|17 March 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Manpreet Bambra}}\n| {{Anchor|Anjli}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Manny}}\n| {{nowrap|24 March 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Steffan Peddie}}\n| {{Anchor|Manny}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Amir Tako}}\n| {{nowrap|31 March 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Uncredited}}\n| {{Anchor|Amir}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Mimi Blunt}}\n| {{nowrap|27 October 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Stirling Gallacher]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Mimi}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Sally Harper}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | {{nowrap|3 November 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Samantha Morris}}\n| {{Anchor|Sally Harper}} rowspan=\"3\" | Samantha and Dom are the potential adoptive parents of [[#Billie Trent|Billie Trent]] (Gwen Currant) and [[#Toni Trent|Toni Trent]] (Nelly Currant). When Billie and Toni return from their house, Floss plants the doubt that Toni isn't keen on the adoption and Floss tells Billie that she has to make sure that Toni doesn't change her mind. Billie and Floss try to convince Toni that living with lots of other people is annoying. Toni announces to Billie that she doesn't want to be fostered and Billie and Floss lock Toni in the shed, so Billie pretends to be herself and Toni to the social worker, Diane. When Toni gets out of the shed, Diane realises what Billie has done and Billie and Toni are both annoyed with each other. Toni refuses to talk to Billie aFloss tells Toni that despite having a mother, she would like a family. When the Harper's visit so Billie can talk to them, Toni decides she wants to live with the Harper's and they move in with the Harper's.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Dom Harper}}\n| {{nowrap|Phil Yarrow}}\n| {{Anchor|Dom Harper}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Diane}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Poppy Jhakra]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Diane}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Police Officer Sykes}}\n| {{nowrap|10 November 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Dylan Barnes}}\n| {{Anchor|Sykes}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Josh}}\n| {{nowrap|17 November 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Bailey Hayden}}\n| {{Anchor|Josh}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|TV Journalist}}\n| {{nowrap|8\u201315 December 2017}}\n| {{nowrap|Rayna Campbell}}\n| {{Anchor|Journalist}}\n|}\n\n===Series 6 (2018)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Character\n! Date(s)\n! Actor\n! Circumstances\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Hilde \"Shaz\"}}\n| {{nowrap|12 January 2018}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Lauren Drummond]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Hilde}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Grant}}\n| {{nowrap|12\u201319 January 2018}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Ian Reddington]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Grant}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Billy McLaine}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|{{nowrap|2 February 2018}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Gary Lucy]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Billy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|[[Gary Linekar]]}}\n| {{nowrap|Himself}}\n| {{Anchor|Gary}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Emi}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|{{nowrap|23 February 2018}}\n| {{nowrap|Lucy Goodings}}\n| {{Anchor|Emi}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Amelie}}\n| {{nowrap|Anya Jurowska}}\n| {{Anchor|Amelie}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Burglar}}\n| rowspan=\"3\"|{{nowrap|23 March 2018}}\n| {{nowrap|Uncredited}}\n| {{Anchor|Burglar}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Brandon}}\n| {{nowrap|Kelton Hoyland}}\n| {{Anchor|Brandon}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|BBC News Reporter}}\n| {{nowrap|Colin Briggs}}\n| {{Anchor|BBC News Reporter}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|John}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|{{nowrap|21 September 2018}}\n| {{nowrap|Micky Cochrane}}\n| {{Anchor|John}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Jacinda}}\n| {{nowrap|Kate Victors}}\n| {{Anchor|Jacinda}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| {{nowrap|Mavis Crinkle}}\n| {{nowrap|28 September 2018}}\n| {{nowrap|[[Annette Badland]]}}\n| {{Anchor|Mavis}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of The Story of Tracy Beaker (franchise) characters]]\n* [[List of The Story of Tracy Beaker characters]]\n* [[List of Tracy Beaker Returns characters]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Tracy Beaker series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dumping Ground, The}}\n[[Category:Children's television characters by series]]\n[[Category:Lists of British television series characters]]\n[[Category:Tracy Beaker series characters| ]]\n[[Category:The Dumping Ground characters| ]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", 